Thomas Hartleb, News24Johannesburg - A Johannesburg metro police officer was shot and injured while stopping a hijacking in Mayfair on Friday afternoon, a spokesperson said.Two officers saw an armed man pulling a driver out of a silver Audi on the corner of Hanover Street and 12th Avenue around 16:00, Chief Superintendent Wayne Minnaar said.A shootout broke out when the officers intervened. One officer was shot in the left hand. The would-be hijacker fled in a gold-coloured VW Golf. No arrests had been made.The Audi driver was in shock, but otherwise unhurt.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.